In this article, President Biden speaks at the Clayco construction site in Elk Grove Village, Illinois, thanking the company for its efforts in combating the COVID-19 pandemic. He emphasizes the importance of treating workers with dignity and the role of unions in building the middle class. He also discusses his administration's efforts to increase vaccination rates, including requirements for federal workers, contractors, and military personnel. Biden highlights the positive impact of vaccination requirements on increasing vaccination rates and returning people to work. He calls on more employers to implement vaccination requirements and emphasizes the broad public support for vaccinations. Biden concludes by urging individuals who haven't been vaccinated to get vaccinated for their own sake and the sake of their families. He also mentions the U.S.'s commitment to providing vaccines to other countries.